wikipedia_page.main: Cyrus Cincinato Cuneo  (18 June 1879 – 23 July 1916), known as Ciro, was an artist, born into an Italian American family of artists and musicians. His parents were Giovanni (John) and Annie Cuneo; his brothers Rinaldo (1877-1939) and Egisto (1890–1972), and his son Terence Cuneo (1907–1996) also became artists.
